#! /bin/bash

# x11docker
# Run GUI applications and desktop environments in docker on a separate X server.
# Provides GPU acceleration and pulseaudio sound. Circumvents some X security leaks.
# Type 'x11docker --help' or scroll down to read usage information.
# https://github.com/mviereck/x11docker

Version="2.2.0"
# ToDo:
# - set default for --glamor
# - check or dismiss developer option --tcp, seems to be broken
# - check if X extension Security is critical and can be dismissed
# - --xpra-image/--xorg-image/--xdummy-image check:
#     --tcp, --exe, --LOG 
#     trusted cookie needed, why?
# - --xpra/--xpra-image: check --mmap, check further options
# - develop new options --xpra-proxy or --xorg-proxy ?
# - avoid tail kill message
# - test --gpu and --virtualgl with different setups of graphics cards and drivers. 
#   Known to work with Intel and AMD onboard chips with open source drivers.
# - check pulseaudio: daemon on host seems to quit when image terminates. 
#   As a workaround, tcp module is not disabled on exit for now
# - check whether VT is not in use with --xorg
# - kaptain sometimes sleeps a while until command is created. no cpu usage. why?
# - try to integrate Alsa sound

# x11docker changelog
# 08.03.2017 V2.2.0   bugfix #8: change : to - in homefolder name (option --home)
# 07.03.2017          show xmessage on errors if not running in terminal
